faq.question: Q: Why are all sorting methods in History not showing up?
faq.answer: A: if all sorting methods arent showing up, it is because you have some hours stored in the time format. The SQLite database in which hours are stored can not sort the entries if they are not in decimal format.

faq.question: Q: Why is the system theming option not showing up in the Appearance Settings?
faq.answer: A: If you are not on Android 12 or later, the system theming option will not show up. Because prior version didn't have the System Theming API.

faq.question: Q: How do i report a bug?
faq.answer: A: Go to the Settings tab via the navigation bar at the bottom, then click on report a bug and create a new issue in the Github repository.

faq.question: Q: What is System Theming?
faq.answer: A: It is a feature of Android 12. It uses Googles new Theming API and will set the accent colors of the app to match your wallpaper. (Only Available on Android 12+)

faq.question: Q: Why are some items showing up green and some red in the App News view?
faq.answer: A: Because if that item has been added or resolved it will change color respectively.
